a single word you've ever

01:59:11.496 --> 01:59:17.816
heard before, because English is unimaginably
rich. I grew up in a house where

01:59:18.796 --> 01:59:22.556
everybody read literature all the
time. I had three sisters and

01:59:22.616 --> 01:59:26.546
a, and then a brother, and we all
read literature. We went to the

01:59:26.596 --> 01:59:30.296
library every week, read lots and lots and
lots of books. So we all had really good

01:59:30.776 --> 01:59:33.036
vocabulary.

01:59:34.356 --> 01:59:38.226
That's how you get vocabulary. Otherwise
you don't, because in conversation,

01:59:38.226 --> 01:59:42.156
"Do you want more tea?" All this sort of stuff,
you don't learn new vocabulary. You have to

01:59:42.175 --> 01:59:46.236
get it from reading and
listening to proper stuff.

01:59:46.296 --> 01:59:50.076
- Which is a very important aspect of vocabulary,
why it's important to know a lot of

01:59:50.096 --> 01:59:53.925
words and to speak clearly,
because those words

01:59:53.976 --> 01:59:56.396
also define the quality of your thoughts.

01:59:56.436 --> 01:59:56.656
- Sure

01:59:56.665 --> 01:59:57.756
- at the end of the day.

01:59:57.776 --> 02:00:01.675
- That's exactly right. I
must say, I think it is a

02:00:01.756 --> 02:00:05.736
